node.text: While developing other potato salad recipes, test kitchen cooks found that seasoning the potatoes while they're hot maximizes flavor. So as we developed our all-American potato salad recipe, we splashed hot russet potatoes with white vinegar and found them to be more flavorful than other types of potatoes treated the same way. Get our All-American Potato Salad recipe by clicking the link in our profile.

node.text: We know what you’re thinking: A recipe for a tomato sandwich? Just trust us here. To make the best tomato sandwich ever but also stay true to the classic, we turned to heirloom tomatoes, hearty white sandwich bread, and a good old mayonnaise. We gave the tomatoes a quick marinade and then used that marinade to further flavor the mayonnaise. Get our recipe by clicking the link in our profile.
